properties.description: Posted by Mbaum22Home to the world famous chicken joint, Walsh\'s, Burksville sits at the crossroads of KK & Kaskaskia Roads. Burksville is growing, thanks to the development of a pair of subdivisions of new homes.

properties.name: Burksville Station
properties.description: Posted by Mbaum22Sort of a suburb of Burksville, this little burgh used to be the site of a station stop on the old Union Pacific line that ran through Monroe County. The old stationhouse, which still stands at the corner of KK and Sportsman Roads, later became a tavern. The railroad disappeared and most of the town did too.

properties.name: Mitchie
properties.description: Posted by Mbaum22The seat of Mitchie Township. John Niebruegge, Mitchie resident, famously drove a "Mitchie Police Department" themed cruiser in the Monroe County Fair Demolition Derby a few years ago. The car rolled over three times and caught on fire twice. John, happily, emerged unscathed. He returned with the car the following year, with similar results. I believe the car has been retired to his Uncle Ronnie\'s pasture.
